In classical mathematics, the exponential function is defined as: expâ¡(z)=ez=âˆ‘n=0âˆžznn!\exp(z) = e^z = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{z^n}{n!}exp(z)=ez=âˆ‘n=0âˆžâ€‹n!znâ€‹
