The left plot shows the real part of the Hypermorphic Zeta function.
The right plot displays the imaginary part of the function.
The function exhibits oscillatory behavior, with both real and imaginary parts showing complex variations as the imaginary part of sss increases. This dynamic behavior is influenced by the modulation functions Ï•\phiÏ• and Ïˆ\psiÏˆ, which allow for additional flexibility and potentially unique patterns in the location of zeros.
